The paper deals with the computation of persistent homology for large datasets, which is a topic in computational topology. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses parallelization and memory access, which suggests categories such as cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of algebraic tools and techniques from computational commutative algebra suggests categories such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
